{
  "ID": "GoR_MinnesotaTribe_DestroyBase_ArmageddonsFall",
  "contractName": "Armageddon's Fall",
  "contractDisplayStyle": "BaseCampaignNormal",
  "difficulty": 14,
  "difficultyUIModifier": 0,
  "weight": 1,
  "scope": "STANDARD",
  "finalDifficulty": 0,
  "representativeCastDefIDOverride": "castDef_MarcusHammerick",
  "shortDescription": "The Armageddon production facility stands before you. Inside, Joanna McEvedy has deployed [[DM.Factions[faction_RemembranceCell],Remembrance Cell's]] prototype superheavy weapons platform along with every remaining warrior loyal to her vision. This is her final stand, this is where the weapon either is destroyed or destroys everyone else.\n\nPrimary objectives are threefold. First, eliminate Joanna McEvedy herself to ensure she cannot rebuild or continue this project. Second, destroy the Armageddon prototype before it can be used or its technology recovered. Third, demolish the production facility to erase all physical evidence of its construction methods and technical specifications.\n\nYour forces are already damaged from breaching the perimeter defenses. Environmental conditions on <i>Fröislandis VII</i> continue to degrade combat effectiveness.\n\nJoanna will deploy the Armageddon prototype in combat defense of the facility. This superheavy mech exceeds all known design limitations and incorporates unknown weapon systems designated Project Rotating Fury. Expect capabilities beyond standard combat parameters.\n\nRemaining Remembrance Cell forces represent the most fanatical believers in Joanna's ideology. They view this weapon as their people's only guarantee of survival and will defend it with suicidal determination. They know what failure means. So do you.\n\nFailure results in immediate nuclear detonation. Marcus Hammerick has a two hundred gigaton warhead prepared for deployment if the facility cannot be secured. Everyone on <i>Fröislandis VII</i> dies if you fail. Win or die, there can be no other outcomes.",
  "longDescription": "This is it, boss. Joanna, the prototype, and the facility. We destroy all three or Marcus detonates the warhead and kills everyone on this planet. Final mission. Win or we all die.",
  "salvagePotential": 22,
